{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 When to Use Each\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Choose Relational Databases when:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab You require high data integrity and stable structure.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Use cases: Finance, HR systems, ERP, healthcare, compliance-based systems.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Choose NoSQL Databases when:\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab You manage large, dynamic, or unstructured data that scales globally.\line \par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 \endash \tx360\tab Use cases: Web apps, IoT, e-commerce analytics, social platforms.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 \bullet \tx360\tab Modern Approach:\line Many modern systems combine both \u8212- an RDBMS for transactions and a NoSQL database for scalability and analytics (polyglot persistence).\sa180\par}
